videos.title: Introduction to Superconductivity - Part 1
videos.description: This lecture covers the basic principles of superconductivity including zero resistance and the Meissner effect.

transcript.text: Welcome to this lecture on superconductivity. Today we'll explore the fascinating phenomenon where certain materials exhibit zero electrical resistance when cooled below a critical temperature. We'll start with the historical discovery by Heike Kamerlingh Onnes in 1911...

videos.title: High-Temperature Superconductors Explained
videos.description: Deep dive into high-temperature superconductors, including cuprates and iron-based superconductors.

transcript.text: High-temperature superconductors revolutionized the field when they were discovered in 1986. Unlike conventional superconductors that require liquid helium cooling, these materials can operate at temperatures achievable with liquid nitrogen...
